\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. A. corymbosa} Griseb.,{\i  Spicil. Fl. Rumel. }{\b 1}: 271 (1843) ({\i Alyssum corymbosum} (Griseb.) Boiss.). Stems 20-50 cm; hairs branched or more or less stellate. Basal leaves oblanceolate to lanceolate or obovate, entire or sinuate-dentate. Inflorescence corymbose. Sepals (1·5-)2-2·5 mm; petals c. 4 mm, bifid, yellow. Silicula (3·5-)4·5-5·5 mm, orbicular to elliptic-orbicular, glabrous; valves strongly inflated; style 1-2 mm. Seeds 1·7-2·5 mm, 2-4 in each loculus; wing 0·2-0·5 mm wide. 2n = 16.{\i  Rocks. • W. & S. part of Balkan peninsula}. Al Gr Ju.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. A. gionae} (Quézel & Contandriopoulos) Greuter & Burdet,{\i  Willdenowia}{\b  13}: 86 (1983) ({\i Alyssum gionae} Quézel & Contandriopoulos). Like {\b 1} but basal leaves longer, oblanceolate to linear-lanceolate; inflorescence more or less paniculate; petals 4-5·5 mm; silicula 6-11(-13) mm; seeds 3-4·5 mm, (2-)4(-6) in each loculus, the wing (0·2-)0·5-1 mm wide. 2n = 16.{\i  Limestone rocks above} 1800{\i  m. • N.W. & C. Greece.} Gr.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Perhaps only subspecifically distinct from {\b 1}.
