\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. A. saxatilis} (L.) Desv., {\i Jour. Bot. Appl.}{\b  3}: 162 (1815) ({\i Alyssum saxatile} L.). Plant 10-40(-50) cm, often woody at the base; hairs stellate. Basal leaves obovate to oblanceolate, sinuate-pinnatifid to entire. Inflorescence corymbose. Sepals 2-3(-4) mm; petals 3-6(-8) mm, yellow, emarginate or bifid. Silicula glabrous; valves almost flat. Seeds 2-2·7 mm, 2 in each loculus; wing 0·3-1·1 mm wide.{\i  Limestone rocks. C. & S.E. Europe, extending to S.W. Italy.} Al Au Bu Cr Cz Ge Gr Hu It Ju Po Rm Rs(W, E) Tu [Ga].
